k%20helps%20businesses%20perform%20better.%C2%A0%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EPage%20focuses%20on%20creating%20clarity%2C%20focus%2C%20and%20alignment%20at%20Chubb.%C2%A0%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EThere's%20no%20rest%20for%20the%20weary%2C%20Darryl%20Page%20told%20me%20during%20the%20second%20week%20of%202024.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe's%20vice%20president%20and%20chief%20culture%20officer%20at%20the%20insurance%20giant%20Chubb%2C%20and%20diversity%2C%20equity%2C%20and%20inclusion%20work%20falls%20under%20his%20remit.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPage%20told%20me%20he%20is%20focused%20on%20having%20engaging%20conversations%20at%20Chubb%20around%20DEI.%20%26quot%3BI%20think%20a%20view%20that%20this%20work%20is%20racist%20is%2C%20in%20my%20mind%2C%20misguided%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20think%20you%20have%20to%2C%20maybe%2C%20put%20the%20rhetoric%20aside%20and%20deal%20with%20the%20absolute%20facts%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%20In%20recent%20weeks%2C%20there%20has%20been%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fbill-ackman-says-dei-is-racist-2024-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EDEI%20backlash%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20including%20tweets%20between%20corporate%20bigwigs%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Felon-musk-duking-it-out-mark-cuban-dei-and-racism-2024-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Esuch%20as%20Elon%20Musk%20and%20Mark%20Cuban%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E.%20%26quot%3BThe%20facts%20would%20suggest%20that%20this%20work%20has%20value%2C%20and%20it%20brings%20value%20to%20the%20organization%20and%20to%20the%20corporations%20that%20are%20engaged%20in%20it%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDEI%20work%20helps%20businesses%20perform%20better%2C%20%26quot%3Bas%20well%20as%20being%20the%20right%20thing%20to%20do%2C%26quot%3B%20Page%20said%2C%20pointing%20out%20that%20%26quot%3Bpeople%20start%20out%20from%20different%20places%20and%20have%20different%20life%20experiences.%26quot%3B%20He%20said%20there's%20an%20important%20difference%20between%20equality%20and%20equity.%20Page%20used%20an%20example%20of%20walking%20into%20a%20room%20of%20people%20and%20giving%20them%20all%20a%20pair%20of%20size%2010%20shoes.%20That's%20equality%2C%20he%20said.%20While%20everyone%20has%20shoes%2C%20it%20doesn't%20work%20if%20you're%20not%20size%2010.%20%26quot%3BBut%20if%20you're%20going%20to%20treat%20people%20equitably%2C%20you're%20going%20to%20walk%20into%20that%20room%20and%20give%20them%20the%20shoes%20that%20fit%20their%20feet%2C%26quot%3B%20Page%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI'm%20an%20advocate%20of%20treating%20people%20equitably%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BCompanies%20that%20embrace%20these%20concepts%20outperform%2C%26quot%3B%20Page%20explained.%20%26quot%3BI%20think%20it's%20important%20that%20the%20work%20proceed.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EThe%20following%20conversation%20has%20been%20edited%20for%20length%20and%20clarity.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EWhat%20do%20you%20do%3F%20Your%20title%20is%20unique.%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI'm%20the%20chief%20culture%20officer.%20What%20that%20really%20focuses%20on%20is%2C%20overall%2C%20the%20care%20and%20feeding%20of%20the%20company's%20culture.%20It's%20a%20conversation%20about%20employee%20engagement.%20It's%20a%20conversation%20about%20how%20we%20understand%20and%20how%20we%20live%20into%20the%20key%20tenants%20of%20what%20our%20cultural%20dynamic%20is.%20I%20actually%20think%20that%20the%20culture%20of%20Chubb%20is%20fairly%20unique.%20We%20talk%20about%20culture%20in%20the%20context%20of%20it's%20what%20we%20practice.%20It's%20who%20we%20are.%20It's%20the%20behaviors%20we%20expect.%20And%20it's%20what%20we%20reward%20and%20recognize%20as%20a%20part%20of%20how%20we%20do%20our%20business%20on%20an%20ongoing%20basis.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EWhy%20did%20you%20take%20on%20this%20role%3F%20What%20change%20did%20you%20hope%20to%20make%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI've%20been%20in%20the%20insurance%20industry%20for%20more%20than%2040%20years.%20I%20started%20my%20career%20in%201981.%20I%20joined%20Ace%2C%20which%20is%20the%20predecessor%20company%20to%20Chubb%2C%20in%202012.%20I%20ran%20the%20international%20personal-lines%20business%20overseas.%20So%20I%20really%20came%20to%20this%20work%20as%20a%20business%20leader%20with%20a%20lot%20of%20experience%20running%20a%20business.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EInterestingly%20enough%2C%20I%20retired%20from%20the%20company%20in%20July%202022.%20And%20I%20actually%20got%20a%20call%20back%20from%20our%20chairman%20and%20our%20chief%20human%20resources%20officer%2C%20and%20they%20asked%20me%20if%20I%20was%20interested%20in%20rejoining%20the%20company%20to%20take%20on%20this%20role%20of%20the%20chief%20culture%20officer.%20After%20some%20back%20and%20forth%20and%20some%20dialogue%2C%20and%20after%20some%20personal%20issues%20that%20I%20navigated%20through%2C%20I%20was%20excited%20to%20be%20able%20to%20rejoin%20and%20take%20on%20this%20opportunity.%20I%20felt%20like%20there%20was%20an%20opportunity%20for%20me%20to%20make%20a%20contribution%20in%20a%20way%20that%20would%20help%20Chubb's%20cultural%20identity%20get%20better%20aligned%20with%20its%20business%20identity%20in%20the%20marketplace.%20So%20that's%20really%20my%20story%2C%20and%20it's%20why%20I%20came%20back%20from%20retirement.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EYou%20talked%20about%20the%20culture%20of%20who%20the%20company%20is%20%E2%80%94%20and%20your%20workers%20%E2%80%94%20and%20then%20your%20business%20and%20clients.%20How%20are%20you%20measuring%20those%20two%20things%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20talked%20about%20Chubb's%20culture%20being%20unique.%20We%20do%20business%20in%2054%20countries%20and%20territories%20around%20the%20world.%20We%20operate%20in%2030%20different%20languages%2C%20minimally.%20We%20have%20three%20main%20pillars%20of%20our%20business%3A%20commercial%20lines%2C%20personal%20lines%2C%20and%20accident%20and%20health.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20you%20think%20about%20all%20the%20different%20combinations%20of%20those%20businesses%20that%20we%20operate%2C%20we%20probably%20have%20over%20200%20different%20product%20combinations.%20And%20so%20when%20you%20think%20about%2054%20countries%20and%20territories%2C%20200%20different%20product%20combinations%2C%2030%20different%20languages%2C%20diversity%20and%20inclusion%20is%20at%20the%20core%20of%20how%20we%20do%20our%20business%20globally.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20opportunity%2C%20I%20think%2C%20to%20mesh%20these%20two%20things%20is%20to%20find%20a%20way%20to%20do%20our%20cultural%20work%20in%20the%20same%20way%20in%20which%20we%20do%20our%20business%20work.%20In%20my%20mind%2C%20one%20of%20the%20real%20key%20attributes%20I%20think%20that%20I%20have%20an%20opportunity%20to%20bring%20to%20this%20work%20is%20to%20create%20clear%20pathways%20to%20better%20integrate%20these%20two%20things%20so%20that%20it's%20not%20separate%20work%2C%20but%20it's%20central%20to%20how%20we%20do%20what%20we%20do%20every%20day.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EWas%20there%20a%20moment%20when%20you%20thought%2C%20%26quot%3BI%20need%20to%20do%20more%3F%20I%20need%20to%20have%20a%20bigger%20impact.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20think%20it%20first%20occurred%20to%20me%20right%20after%20George%20Floyd's%20murder.%20As%20you%20can%20imagine%2C%20a%20number%20of%20different%20companies%20were%20having%20very%20different%20conversations%20and%20I%20was%20approached%20by%20my%20predecessor%20in%20this%20role%20as%20a%20business%20leader%20in%20the%20organization%20to%20participate%20on%20a%20panel%20that%20was%20going%20to%20be%20part%20of%20a%20global%20broadcast%2C%20to%20talk%20about%20some%20of%20the%20issues%20that%20I%20experienced%20as%20a%20Black%20man%20in%20this%20industry%20for%2040%20years.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20subject%20matter%20was%20pretty%20raw%20and%20pretty%20clear%20to%20me.%20What%20I%20experienced%20after%20I%20spent%20an%20hour%20and%20a%20half%20on%20this%20discussion%20with%20my%20colleagues%20is%20I%20started%20getting%20phone%20calls%20and%20interactions%20from%20people%2C%20some%20of%20whom%20worked%20as%20part%20of%20my%20team%2C%20others%20that%20I%20had%20only%20met%20on%20a%20couple%20of%20occasions%2C%20but%20they%20were%20reaching%20out%20to%20me%20and%20wanting%20to%20have%20a%20conversation%20with%20me.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20think%20there%20was%20something%20about%20that%2C%20which%20helped%20me%20understand%20that%20there%20was%20a%20story%20I%20could%20tell.%20There%20was%20work%20I%20could%20do%20to%20help%20create%20a%20little%20clarity%2C%20a%20little%20focus%2C%20and%20a%20little%20alignment%20around%20how%20we%20can%20get%20some%20things%20done.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI've%20been%20involved%20in%20this%20work%20in%20the%20periphery%20for%20as%20long%20as%20I've%20been%20in%20the%20industry.%20When%20I%20started%20in%20this%20industry%2C%20in%201981%2C%20it%20was%20not%20unusual%20to%20walk%20into%20a%20room%20and%20be%20the%20only%20Black%20man.%20And%20the%20interesting%20thing%20about%20it%20is%20that%20there%20are%20still%20some%20rooms%20that%20I%20can%20walk%20into%20today%2C%20in%202023%2C%20where%20that's%20still%20the%20case.%20So%20there's%20a%20lot%20of%20work%20to%20do.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ECan%20you%20recall%20a%20moment%20when%20you%20were%20dismissed%20and%20you%20had%20to%20stand%20up%20for%20yourself%20or%20you%20had%20to%20find%20your%20voice%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThey're%20probably%20too%20numerous%20to%20count%2C%20to%20be%20really%20honest%20with%20you.%20There%20are%20a%20few%20instances%20where%20there's%20important%20business%20information%20that%20you%20need%20to%20impart%2C%20and%20you%20may%20have%20a%20difficult%20time%20getting%20the%20attention%20of%20leadership.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEarly%20in%20my%20career%2C%20I%20experienced%20those%20types%20of%20situations.%20What%20was%20really%20interesting%20to%20me%2C%20and%20I%20think%20it's%20still%20a%20hallmark%20of%20how%20I%20try%20to%20do%20what%20I%20can%20today%2C%20is%20you%20have%20to%20find%20a%20way.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESometimes%20when%20you%20walk%20into%20the%20room%20and%20you%20want%20to%20have%20a%20direct%20conversation%2C%20and%20people%20are%20preoccupied%20with%20other%20things%20and%20other%20circumstances%2C%20you%20don't%20have%20their%20full%20attention%2C%20or%20you're%20not%20getting%20the%20listening%20that%20you%20want.%20Sometimes%20when%20people%20do%20that%2C%20and%20they%20get%20dismissed%20or%20they%20don't%20get%20the%20hearing%20that%20they%20want%20to%20have%2C%20they%20give%20up.%20I%20think%20the%20challenge%20around%20this%20is%20that%20if%20you're%20really%20committed%20to%20your%20view%20on%20this%2C%20then%20you%20have%20to%20find%20a%20different%20way.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20worked%20for%20a%20boss%20early%20in%20my%20career%20who%20I%20had%20this%20experience%20with%2C%20and%20I%20found%20out%20that%20he%20read%20everything.%20I'd%20go%20to%20his%20office%20and%20talk%20to%20him%20and%20try%20to%20accomplish%20what%20I%20needed%20to%20accomplish.%20I%20got%20kicked%20out%20a%20couple%20of%20times.%20So%20I%20decided%20to%20write%20a%20memo%20to%20a%20couple%20of%20my%20colleagues%20and%20copied%20him%20on%20it.%20It%20wasn't%20a%20day%20later%20when%20he%20came%20to%20my%20office%20and%20said%2C%20%26quot%3BIs%20this%20what%20you%20were%20trying%20to%20tell%20me%3F%26quot%3B%20And%20I%20said%2C%20%26quot%3BYeah%2C%20actually%20it%20is.%26quot%3B%20He%20said%2C%20%26quot%3BWell%2C%20this%20is%20really%20critically%20important.%26quot%3B%20And%20I%20said%2C%20%26quot%3BYeah%2C%20I%20think%20so.%26quot%3B%20And%20he%20said%2C%20%26quot%3BI%20wish%20you%20would%20have%20worked%20a%20little%20bit%20harder%20to%20try%20to%20make%20sure%20I%20understood%20this.%26quot%3B%20And%20I%20said%2C%20%26quot%3BWell%2C%20I%20think%20I%20did.%26quot%3B%20I%20said%2C%20%26quot%3BYou%20know%2C%20you%20tossed%20me%20out%20of%20your%20office%20a%20couple%20of%20times%2