the%20clip%20that%20in%20Germany%20people%20have%20to%20buy%20their%20own%20washers%20and%20dryers%20even%20if%20they're%20renting%20an%20apartment%2C%20and%20added%20the%20communal%20dryer%20was%20%26quot%3Bperfect%26quot%3B%20for%20people%20who%20can't%20afford%20their%20own%20machines.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20a%20November%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.tiktok.com%2F%40roberts2.00%2Fvideo%2F7300607242351496494%3Fq%3DUSA%2520culture%2520shock%2520dryer%26t%3D1702550735654%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Epost%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20a%20Latvian%20creator%20said%20that%20after%20being%20used%20to%20hanging%20clothes%20on%20a%20drying%20rack%2C%20he's%20noticed%20that%20the%20process%20of%20doing%20laundry%20is%20considerably%20quicker%20in%20the%20US%20because%20he%20can%20use%20a%20dryer.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt's%20very%20convenient%20and%20it's%20great%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EThere%20are%20a%20few%20theories%20as%20to%20why%20hang%20drying%20seems%20to%20be%20more%20popular%20in%20Europe%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3ETikTokers'%20assessment%20that%20dryers%20are%20way%20more%20common%20in%20the%20US%20seems%20accurate.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%202021's%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.census.gov%2Fprograms-surveys%2Fahs%2Fdata%2Finteractive%2Fahstablecreator.html%3Fs_areas%3D00000%26s_year%3D2021%26s_tablename%3DTABLE3%26s_bygroup1%3D1%26s_bygroup2%3D1%26s_filtergroup1%3D1%26s_filtergroup2%3D1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EAmerican%20Housing%20Survey%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%2084%25%20of%20respondents%20said%20they%20had%20access%20to%20a%20dryer%20at%20home%2C%20echoing%20a%202018%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.sciencedirect.com%2Fscience%2Farticle%2Fabs%2Fpii%2FS1359431117315132%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eresearch%20paper%20in%20the%20Applied%20Thermal%20Engineering%20journal%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20listed%20the%20proportion%20of%20US%20households%20with%20clothes%20dryers%20at%20over%2080%25.%20A%202023%20article%20from%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fenergy.ec.europa.eu%2Fnews%2Fcommission-announces-new-ecodesign-and-energy-labelling-rules-household-tumble-dryers-2023-11-22%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EEuropean%20Commission%3C%2Fa%3E%20stated%20that%20the%20number%20of%20household%20dryers%20across%20the%20European%20Union%20was%20around%2060%20million%2C%20which%20amounts%20to%20around%2030%25%20of%20a%20total%20of%20200%20million%20households%2C%20according%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fec.europa.eu%2Feurostat%2Fweb%2Fproducts-eurostat-news%2Fw%2Fedn-20231120-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E2022%20EU%20data%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThere%20are%20several%20reasons%20why%20there%20are%20fewer%20dryers%20in%20Europe%20than%20the%20US%2C%20according%20to%20Ruth%20Schwartz%20Cowan%2C%20a%20history%20and%20sociology%20of%20science%20professor%20at%20the%20University%20of%20Pennsylvania%2C%20who%20authored%20%26quot%3BMore%20Work%20for%20Mother%3A%20The%20Ironies%20of%20Household%20Technology%20from%20the%20Open%20Hearth%20to%20the%20Microwave%26quot%3B%20and%20%26quot%3BA%20Social%20History%20of%20American%20Technology.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAmong%20the%20reasons%20she%20mentioned%20over%20email%20correspondence%20with%20BI%20were%20that%20European%20kitchens%20and%20bathrooms%20are%20often%20smaller%2C%20so%20a%20washer%20can%20fit%2C%20but%20not%20a%20dryer.%20She%20also%20said%20that%20as%20the%20housing%20stock%20in%20Europe%20is%20typically%20much%20older%2C%20it's%20sometimes%20difficult%20to%20vent%20a%20dryer%20to%20the%20outside.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHang%20drying%20may%20also%20be%20a%20preferred%20choice%20in%20some%20countries%20because%20of%20cultural%20ideas%20about%20cleanliness%20and%20comfort%2C%20according%20to%20Kirstin%20Munro%2C%20an%20assistant%20professor%20of%20economics%20at%20the%20New%20School%20for%20Social%20Research%20in%20New%20York%20and%20author%20of%20%26quot%3BThe%20Production%20of%20Everyday%20Life%20in%20Eco-Conscious%20Households.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMunro%20said%20she%20previously%20conducted%20research%20interviews%20with%20a%20total%20of%2041%20eco-conscious%20households%20in%20the%20UK%20and%20US%2C%20and%20said%20UK%20interviewees%20told%20her%20that%20they%20felt%20a%20machine-dried%20towel%20doesn't%20dry%20them%20properly%20or%20feels%20sticky%2C%20so%20they%20had%20a%20preference%20for%20line-dried%20towels.%20US%20households%20had%20a%20preference%20for%20machine-dried%20towels.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMunro%20said%20she%20found%20that%2C%20%26quot%3BWith%20the%20US%20households%2C%20even%20the%20households%20who%20are%20trying%20to%20reduce%20their%20use%20of%20energy%2C%20the%20majority%20of%20the%20ones%20I%20spoke%20with%20still%20tumble%20dry%20their%20laundry.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20discrepancy%20is%20down%20to%20historical%20norms%2C%20Munro%20said%2C%20which%20differ%20across%20geographical%20regions.%20At%20the%20end%20of%20the%20day%2C%20%26quot%3BWhat%20you're%20used%20to%20becomes%20normal%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Famericans-europe-culture-shock-laundry-dryer-difference-explained-2023-12%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1705309509000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F657af2f750edbc52a8641dad%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Famericans-europe-culture-shock-laundry-dryer-difference-explained-2023-12%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22People%20who%20have%20moved%20to%20Europe%20from%20the%20US%20often%20comment%20on%20a%20big%20difference%20in%20how%20the%20cultures%20approach%20laundry%2C%20and%20experts%20say%20they're%20not%20imagining%20it.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22ccheong%40insider.com%20(Charissa%20Cheong)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A21%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Famericans-europe-culture-shock-laun