e%20rudder%20bolts.%20Together%2C%20these%20point%20to%20a%20common%20problem%3A%20the%20company's%20once-vaunted%20system%20for%20building%20its%20prized%20737s%20has%20been%20badly%20damaged%20by%20worker%20turnover%2C%20supplier%20distress%20and%20the%20shortcomings%20lingering%20from%20the%20breakneck%20production%20last%20decade%20before%20the%20Max%20tragedies%20and%20the%20Covid%20freeze.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThey%20have%20an%20ongoing%20quality%20control%20issue%20and%20it's%20systemic%20and%20it%20runs%20not%20just%20through%20the%20737%20program%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Darren%20Straker%2C%20the%20former%20head%20of%20aircraft%20accident%20investigations%20for%20the%20United%20Arab%20Emirates%20and%20Hong%20Kong%2C%20who%20most%20recently%20worked%20for%20Chinese%20planemaker%20Comac.%20%26quot%3BAnd%20it's%20largely%20due%20to%20the%20fact%20that%20they%20subcontract%20major%20airframe%20component%20manufacturing%20and%20quality%20control%20to%20their%20independent%20contractors.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAirbus%20has%20gone%20the%20other%20way%20in%20recent%20years%2C%20opting%20to%20keep%20more%20in-house.%20The%20reversal%20came%20after%20Faury%20declared%20aerostructures%20to%20be%20part%20of%20the%20%26quot%3Bcore%26quot%3B%20business%2C%20and%20that%20keeping%20them%20would%20increase%20efficiency.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt%20is%20time%20to%20re-examine%20the%20delegation%20of%20authority%20and%20assess%20any%20associated%20safety%20risks%2C%26quot%3B%20FAA%20Administrator%20Mike%20Whitaker%20said%20in%20a%20statement%20announcing%20the%20agency's%20increased%20oversight%20of%20Boeing's%20operations%20on%20Jan.%2012.%20%C2%A0%26quot%3BThe%20grounding%20of%20the%20737-9%20and%20the%20multiple%20production-related%20issues%20identified%20in%20recent%20years%20require%20us%20to%20look%20at%20every%20option%20to%20reduce%20risk.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20FAA%20is%20intensifying%20its%20scrutiny%20after%20coming%20under%20fire%20in%20the%20aftermath%20of%20the%20two%20Max%20crashes%20almost%20five%20years%20ago.%20For%20decades%2C%20the%20FAA%20has%20deputized%20employees%20of%20Boeing%20and%20other%20large%20aerospace%20manufacturers%20to%20act%20on%20the%20agency's%20behalf%20in%20signing%20off%20on%20some%20aspects%20of%20aircraft%20designs.%20Now%20the%20regulator%20is%20considering%20bringing%20in%20a%20third%20party%20to%20independently%20oversee%20Boeing's%20inspections%20and%20quality%20control%2C%20underscoring%20its%20loss%20of%20confidence.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt's%20like%20trying%20to%20raise%20children%20and%20putting%20them%20in%20charge%2C%20and%20it%20has%20not%20worked%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Jim%20Hall%2C%20who%20chaired%20the%20National%20Transportation%20Safety%20Board%20from%201994%20to%202001.%20%26quot%3BIt's%20obvious%20that%20the%20normal%20enforcement%20steps%20that%20have%20been%20in%20place%20have%20failed%20and%20the%20flying%20public%20is%20at%20risk%2C%20and%20we%20can't%20permit%20that%20to%20continue.%26quot%3B%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EGetting%20the%20details%20right%20is%20literally%20a%20matter%20of%20life%20and%20death%20in%20the%20commercial%20aviation%20business.%20A%20typical%20single-aisle%20aircraft%20consists%20of%20more%20than%20400%2C000%20parts%20that%20get%20assembled%20in%20a%20finely%20tuned%20ballet%20of%20bolting%20together%20the%20wings%2C%20main%20tube%20and%20rear%20section%20before%20kitting%20out%20the%20aircraft%20with%20interiors.%20These%20days%2C%20Boeing%20manages%20to%20churn%20out%20about%2038%20units%20on%20a%20monthly%20basis%2C%20a%20production%20rate%20the%20company%20has%20told%20suppliers%20it%20wants%20to%20take%20to%20more%20than%2050%20by%20next%20year.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%3E%3Cimg%20alt%3D%5C%22Latest%20and%20Breaking%20News%20on%20NDTV%5C%22%20title%3D%5C%22Latest%20and%20Breaking%20News%20on%20NDTV%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2024-01%2F0gg87d88_boeing-aircraft-graph-bloomb