esidential%20term%20may%20seem%20like%20a%20victory%2C%20cracks%20in%20the%20foundation%20of%20Taiwan%E2%80%99s%20political%20landscape%20are%20widening.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20roots%20of%20this%20instability%20stretch%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ajpor.org%2Farticle%2F77478-still-aquamarine-china-factor-and-the-2020-election-revisited%5C%22%3Eback%20to%202020%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20where%20anti-establishment%20sentiment%20simmered%20beneath%20the%20surface%2C%20even%20as%20the%20China%20factor%20dominated%20headlines.%20This%20time%2C%20the%20discontent%20is%20boiling%20over.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Democratic%20Progressive%20government%2C%20once%20riding%20a%20wave%20of%20youthful%20support%2C%20now%20faces%20accusations%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.internationalaffairs.org.au%2Faustralianoutlook%2Ftaiwans-2024-presidential-election-amidst-the-division-a-third-wave-emerges%2F%5C%22%3Epower%20abuse%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%2C%20crucially%2C%20a%20failure%20to%20address%20the%20very%20issues%20that%20propelled%20them%20to%20power%20in%202016%3B%20skyrocketing%20housing%20prices%2C%20stagnant%20wages%2C%20and%20widening%20inequality.%20These%20woes%20fuelled%20the%20rise%20of%20the%20Taiwan%20People%E2%80%99s%20Party.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Kuomintang%2C%20the%20other%20pillar%20of%20the%20old%20order%2C%20struggles%20to%20offer%20solutions.%20Their%20proposed%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ffocustaiwan.tw%2Fpolitics%2F202310270021%5C%22%3Esubsidised%20interest%20rates%3C%2Fa%3E%20risk%20further%20inflating%20the%20housing%20bubble%2C%20alienating%20the%20young%20generation%20they%20desperately%20need%20to%20win.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMeanwhile%2C%20the%20Taiwan%20People%E2%80%99s%20Party%20proposes%20alternatives%20%E2%80%93%20public%20housing%2C%20rent%20subsidies%2C%20and%20even%20property%20tax%20hikes%20%E2%80%93%20aimed%20at%20making%20housing%20truly%20affordable.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFor%20decades%2C%20power%20has%20swayed%20between%20the%20Kuomintang%20and%20Democratic%20Progressive%20Party%2C%20yet%20voter%20satisfaction%20with%20Taiwanese%20democracy%20languishes%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fmuse.jhu.edu%2Fpub%2F1%2Farticle%2F753202%5C%22%3Ebelow%2050%25%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20stark%20statistic%20betrays%20a%20profound%20representation%20crisis%2C%20an%20outcry%20against%20the%20established%20parties%2C%20often%20due%20to%20a%20perceived%20failure%20to%20tackle%20core%20issues.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Taiwan%20People%E2%80%99s%20Party%2C%20riding%20this%20wave%20of%20disillusionment%2C%20attracts%20those%20who%20yearn%20for%20a%20political%20shift%2C%20focusing%20on%20domestic%20woes.%20It%20emerges%20as%20a%20beacon%20of%20hope%20for%20those%20who%20have%20lost%20faith%20in%20the%20two-party%20system.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EWhy%20did%20the%20DPP%20win%20again%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.taiwannews.com.tw%2Fen%2Fnews%2F5070525%5C%22%3EPre-election%20polls%3C%2Fa%3E%20painted%20a%20clear%20picture%3A%20more%20than%2060%25%20craved%20a%20change%2C%20a%20break%20from%20the%20Democratic%20Progressive%20Party%E2%80%99s%20grip%20on%20power.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBut%20the%20tide%20of%20discontent%20splintered%2C%20dividing%20voters%20between%20the%20established%20Kuomintang%20and%20the%20rising%20force%20of%20the%20Taiwan%20People%E2%80%99s%20Party.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EYouth%20flocked%20to%20the%20newcomer%2C%20while%20the%20Kuomintang%20found%20favour%20among%20older%20demographics.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETo%20unseat%20the%20government%2C%20a%20united%20front%20seemed%20logical.%20Yet%2C%20cooperation%20crumbled%2C%20replaced%20by%20escalating%20animosity%20between%20the%20opposition%20parties.%20This%20fractured%20landscape%20handed%20the%20ruling%20party%20an%20advantage%3A%20a%20divided%20opposition%20meant%20their%20own%20victory%20was%20practically%20guaranteed.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Kuomintang%2C%20desperate%20to%20tip